name: Jordan Anderson
bio: NASCAR Driver and team owner @jarnascar from South Carolina. Living out Proverbs 3:5-6.. Embrace the journey & never give up.

social_posts.post_text: PRI 22’ in the books 👊🏼

Woke up this morning hoping some news I heard yesterday wasn’t true. Really going to miss this guy. @greg_smilemaker was an amazing soul with a heart for people beyond anyone I’ve ever met before. He was always quick to joke but deep down cared for people with a selfless heart - always putting others first. We always took lots of time talking about all our crazy stories and travels on the road. We had just spent some time together at PRI and talked on Saturday as he was celebrating his birthday helping others. He’d be so pissed knowing I was tearing up writing this grabbing me around the shoulder to tell me he was in a better place. Until we see each other again #bigredcowboyhat 🙏🏼

A week to never forget and a great way to close out 2022. After everything that went on late in the year and having to postpone our honeymoon, thankful @kendallanderson97 and I got to finally celebrate and enjoy a beautiful trip to @lacasadelaplaya 🙏🏼🙏🏼

We’ve come a long way from where this journey started. So thankful to everyone that played a part in making this happen as our team expands to field two full time cars in the Xfinity Series for 2023 with @parkerretzlaff and @jebburtonracing in the @jarnascar Chevy Camaros. Excited would be an understatement to see what this season has in store.

Very cool opportunity today to speak at the Nascar Safety & Operations Summit discussing and sharing perspective on the Talladega crash from October. 

Best part was I got to see and hug the entire @talladega and @nascar safety & rescue group that helped me out that day. 🙏🏼

Such a humbling feeling seeing both of these haulers roll south today to kick off 2023. So many amazing people have played a role in this team growing every year and this next chapter is for sure to be a big one for us. To see the hard work turn our dreams into a reality continues to fuel the push forward. See you soon Daytona 👊🏼

AHHHHHHH

A 4th and 11th to start the year off! 

Thank you @DAYTONA for being a little nicer to us this year 😆

Smiling a little more than I was pre-race after leaving California with two solid finishes and two cars clean ready for this weekends race in Vegas 😆 Thankful for our two drivers @jebburtonracing and @parkerretzlaff that see the big picture and the road map we’ve laid out to keep growing.
Doubles in the Desert ✌🏼
Every day he’s living his best life… Wishing a Happy National Pet Day to Brecks 😆

Thank you all for the birthday wishes today! Wouldn’t want to celebrate another year on earth any other way. Proud of everyone at @jarnascar for believing in the vision and putting a lot of heart into these cars every week. Our guys @parkerretzlaff and @jebburtonracing fought hard all night long and brought us home two more solid finishes. It takes a village and I’m thankful to have our whole team on this journey. 👊🏼
Talladega tomorrow with two fast rides. Ready to see what our guys can make happen 👊🏼👊🏼

Heading down to @TALLADEGA for the first time since last years accident. 🙏🏼

Make sure to catch the @fs1 story they shot this week that will air before our race this Saturday.

Proud would be an understatement after watching our team during qualifying today. Lots of hard work went into these two rides. After all that Talladega put us through last year it really was an amazing feeling to see our cars land 4th and 8th after making it to the 2nd Round of qualifying. Going to be a wild one tomorrow, just hope we’re there at the end! 🙌🏼
We won!!!!!
May you love something as much as Jordan Anderson loves racing.
Special day at the shop celebrating our first team win at @talladega with @jebburtonracing and all our families. So grateful to every single person that’s been on this journey with us.
Appreciate the awesome swag bag @lucasoilproducts 👊🏼👊🏼 Thanks for always keeping our whole team running strong!
Two fast rides loaded up and headed to Darlington! 👊🏼
SHAKE N BAKE 🏁 @xfinityracing @jarnascar @bommaritoautosport
Cool seeing this come together this week with Jeb Burton, Bobby Reuse, Joel Black and Capital City Hauling and Towing for one of the first races back at North Wilkesboro Speedway.
Honored to have the opportunity and freedom to see both of these cars on track this weekend 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

Factory Motor Parts is featured on the rear bumper of this week’s #31 @parkerretzlaff car! We’re ready for a great weekend of racing! Bring on #charlottemotorspeedway 

@jordanandersonracing | #nascar

Proud of everyone at @jarnascar for staying after it through all the highs and lows this year. Today marked the fifth race in a row we had one or both of our cars qualify inside the Top 10. It’s all about the little victories and I’m incredibly thankful for everyone that keeps making this year possible 🙏🏼🙏🏼
Race day at the home track 😆🙌🏼
Two cars in the Top 10! So grateful for every single person on this team. Jeb and Parker were up on the wheel all night 💪🏼
Stay weird Portland ✌🏼

A little west coast swing action 💪🏼

Portland ➡️ STL ➡️ Sonoma
A little throwback… 2009 at Carolina Speedway 😆
Nashville bound with two rockets 🚀

So proud of these guys. 

Never gave up all day. 💪🏼💪🏼

A solid 10th for @parkerretzlaff and a 13th for @jebburtonracing with a car held together by barebond after that early crash
A day full of moving but setup plate #3 has made its way into the building and ready for some new projects 🙌🏼
Always keeping us running strong, @fkrodends will be riding along with us on the 31 for the Chicago road race this weekend 💪🏼💪🏼
Race weekend in the Windy City 💨
This is wild 👀
Engines are primed and ready - practice kicks off at 5PM EST here in New Hampshire.
Race day 👊🏼
Double Top 10 in Michigan! Great job all day by @parkerretzlaff @jebburtonracing and everyone on this team that keeps this journey rolling every week! 🙌🏼

Back behind the wheel! So incredibly grateful for the opportunity to go racing at Daytona later this month with @larrymac28 calling the shots. It’s been an amazing journey seeing our team take off with Jeb and Parker this season, and it’ll be special to get on track with the both of them. After what happened at Talladega last year I’ve gained a greater appreciation for moments like these and definitely am going to make the most of this one.

Lots of really cool things happening at @DAYTONA this weekend for us all.

200th start for our team since we made our debut at the same track back in 2018, and to be back behind the wheel makes it that much more special.

Catch me and @larrymac28 with the 27 this Friday night! 👊🏼

A throwback to dad! 

@jebburtonracing will race with @wardburtonwbwf’s design from his 2002 Daytona 500 win.

A first for our team this weekend in @daytona as we’ll hit the track with 3 cars for Friday nights race while celebrating our 200th start at the same place it all started.

#22 - @jebburtonracing 
#27 - @jordanandersonracing 
#31 - @parkerretzlaff

Sometimes building fast race cars takes a little old school creativity. 

We may have pushed that a little far today, but tomorrow is a new day and still feeling really good about our chances. 

We’ll just have our work cut out for us a little bit early on coming from the back.
Almost go time here in Daytona!

Top 15 finish for all 3 of our cars tonight calls for a celebration. Loved every minute being behind the wheel tonight and forgot how much I missed being out there. So thankful for our amazing team of guys that pulled this weekend off and showed what we’re capable of. Appreciate everyone’s support this weekend!!! 🙌🏼🙌🏼
Daytona photo drop ✌🏼 Thankful for a great weekend and all the amazing friends that have been apart of this journey and start #200 for @jarnascar

So proud of this whole team the last two weeks. A lot of fight and grit to keep making the push they have. Two Top 15s in a row at Kansas and Bristol for Jeb and Parker. 

Behind the scenes yesterday at Bristol we were put behind the 8 ball with a lap 1 crash in practice. Guys from both teams chipped in to take our car from Darlington and get everything swapped over and ready for the race. As drivers intros wrapped up we had just cleared tech with our back up car and rolled to the grid. Both drivers ran hard, smart races. Parker fought a power steering issue the last 50 laps and brought it home 15th while Jeb kept our playoff hopes alive with a 13th as we sit just 4 points below 8th now.

I told my guys yesterday sometimes God puts us in a spot to be setup for a comeback to show what a little faith can do. Building something special here with our team with an even more incredible group of guys.
HQ under the lights ✌🏼

Man…Wild to think it’s already been a year since Talladega… glad to be here today with just some battle scars. 

Still forever grateful to everyone at @talladega and UAB… and you guys for all the prayers that day. 🙏🏼

Glad we’ve got a little better feeling about the place now

That feeling when both cars pass tech 😅

Race day tomorrow in our backyard. Our guys have been working hard to make a strong push to rebound and finish strong these next few weeks. 👊🏼

That Alsco green tho! 💚

#NASCAR | #Alsco302

Racing for a lot of extra special reasons this weekend as we’ll have the names of friends and family members that have dealt with the effects of cancer in its various stages. We hope the 31 on track this weekend will bring those currently fighting extra encouragement and strength as they continue their battle forward.

Lots to be grateful for this season… hard to believe we did our last load up yesterday for Phoenix to mark another year in the books on this journey. It’s been a ride and there are so many people to be thankful for making it all happen. Excited to close out the year this weekend and start prepping for 2024. 🙏🏼

This year, Chevrolet achieved a remarkable feat by securing the NASCAR Cup, Xfinity, and Craftsman Truck Series manufacturers championships! We want to extend our heartfelt gratitude to all the incredible fans who cheered us on throughout 2023 and played a pivotal role in celebrating this monumental achievement. We’re thrilled to be a part of the incredible #TeamChevy community and are joyfully joining in the celebrations with you all. A big congratulations to the talented drivers, dedicated crews, and exceptional teams whose unwavering efforts made this triumph possible!
We’re continuing our growth for 2024! Reach out today to learn about new opportunities within our team.
NASCAR Driver and team owner @jarnascar from South Carolina. Living out Proverbs 3:5-6.. Embrace the journey & never give up.
